data.name: Herb-Crusted Pork Tenderloin with Garlic Mashed Potatoes
data.quickTastyDescription: A savory and tender pork tenderloin coated with fresh herbs, paired with creamy garlic mashed potatoes for a delicious, comforting meal.
detailedCookingInstructions: Rub the pork tenderloin with olive oil, then season with salt and pepper.
Chop the fresh herbs finely and press them onto the pork to coat it evenly.
Place the pork in a baking dish and roast in the oven for about 25-30 minutes, or until the internal temperature reaches 145째F (63째C).
While the pork is baking, peel and chop the potatoes into chunks and boil in salted water until tender (about 15-20 minutes).
In the last 5 minutes of boiling, add the peeled garlic cloves to the pot.
Drain the potatoes and garlic, then return them to the pot. Add butter, milk, salt, and pepper.
Mash the potatoes until smooth and creamy. Adjust seasoning to taste.
Once the pork is done, let it rest for a few minutes before slicing.
Serve the sliced pork tenderloin with garlic mashed potatoes on the side.
data.detailedName: Easy Herb-Crusted Pork Tenderloin with Creamy Garlic Mashed Potatoes
